# linkedin-leads deploy workflow

**Production runs on Hetzner, not the laptop.** Code lives at
`/opt/jobhunt/src/apps/linkedin-leads` on host `hetzner` (SSH alias), checked out from
`github.com/Unobtainiumrock/jobhunt` via read-only deploy key.

## Shipping a code change is TWO steps, not one

```bash
git push origin main    # ship to GitHub
./bin/deploy            # pull + rebuild + restart on Hetzner
```

If you only do step 1, nothing changes in prod. `./bin/deploy` wraps
`ssh hetzner 'cd /opt/jobhunt/src/apps/linkedin-leads && git pull --ff-only && docker compose up -d --build'`.
It is idempotent and safe to re-run.

## Do NOT

- `rsync` / `scp` app code to Hetzner (the rsync path is retired).
- Edit files directly on `/opt/jobhunt/src/apps/linkedin-leads` via SSH (next `git pull`
  will clobber them with a tree-conflict). Push through GitHub instead.
- Weaken the safety rails (`LINKEDIN_SEND_ENABLED` gate,
  `SENDER_RATE_LIMIT`, follow-up cap of 2, abstain-on-dead-end logic)
  without explicit user approval. Compose defaults live sends on; use
  `LINKEDIN_SEND_ENABLED=0` in `.env` only when you intentionally want dry-run.

## Remember

- `.env` is gitignored. Laptop copy and `/opt/jobhunt/src/apps/linkedin-leads/.env` on
  Hetzner are hand-synced with `scp` when values change.
- `profile/user_profile.yaml` is gitignored but MUST exist on Hetzner
  or `score_leads` crashes. If missing: `scp` it over, then rebuild.
- See `AGENTS.md` at repo root for full project context (including **“When
  something breaks or feels stuck”** — symptom → fix playbook for operators).
